translated:
Öster, Johannes Richard, Fil. Lic., substitute teacher at a teaching seminary, Växjö, born on April 16, 1902 in Älvkarleby, Uppsala County, 1st child of clergyman Richard Ö. and Sigrid Almberg. Married in 1938 to Signe Larsson. Children: Bengt-Olof, born in 1939, Marianne, born in 1942. 
Education: Graduated from high school in Stockholm in 1926, Bachelor of Arts in Uppsala in 1931, Fil. Lic. in 1936, served as a trainee in Uppsala from 1937-1938. Temporary lecturer at Uppsala public elementary school from 1931-1932, part-time teacher at Uppsala elementary school from 1932-1938, Uppsala private secondary school from 1933-1934, temporary assistant teacher in Linköping from January 1938, junior assistant from 1939, part-time teacher at Uppsala vocational school from 1938-1939, April 1941 to 1942, Lv.2 1942-1946, Linköping vocational school from 1944-1946, assistant teacher at Växjö preschool teacher training from 1946. 
Also worked as a geologist for the Swedish Geological Survey from 1940. Traveled to Denmark in 1934, Finland in 1936. Written scientific dissertations and papers in geography and quaternary geology.
